title: Grateful Dead Live at Providence Civic Center on 1983-04-20
description: Touch Of Gray-> Promised Land, Loser, Minglewood Blues, Ramble On Rose, Me & My Uncle-> Cumberland Blues, Looks Like Rain, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider My Brother Esau-> Maybe You Know, Bertha-> Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Throwing Stones-> Morning Dew-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Don't Ease Me In

reviews.review_text: Sennheiser or Beyers? I was sixteen when I first got this tape.  Two days after the show.  I had just seen Stills with the Boys a few days earlier.  I was king of the hill with my walkman at the bus stop. I know every note.  I would say the first set is epic, the second set is fair.  One thing is for sure.  The first set is taped with Beyer microphones and the second with Senn 421's.  I had Charlie Miller's labeled master in my hand when my copy was made on 1983-and still do.  Give a listen and you will agree.  Kudos for Charlie for putting this up.  I think he taped the whole tour.

solid show overshadowed by the others on this tour there are elements to all the solid shows of spring 83 here and this was pretty fun to be at  - rowdy from all of the tailgating we got down there mid afternoon and solid b+..... good listen

1983 I like 83' Dead...this is a great 83 show, I mean it's 4-20 for crying out loud...Loser and Cumberland are razor sharp, Looks like Rain has a far out Jerry solo, China-Rider is crisp...second set features an Eyes that although played fast has Jerry contributed just some beautiful licks...Dew is good and T-Stones has a great jam...definitely a good listen...
wats up with the 421's Levels are too low. I love audience recordings. This one could have gone up a notch. Kill first set.
yep way too low, had to shut it down and wait for a better copy i guess.
